2. The Book of the Dead as an Ontological Filter

Modern readers think the Book of the Dead answers:

“What happens after you die?”

Pantheon reading reveals the real question:

“What patterns are allowed to continue?”

The text is not about death.
It’s about selection under transformation.

Key insight:
	•	Survival is not moral
	•	Survival is not granted
	•	Survival is structural viability

That’s the same rule your Pantheon enforces.

